 Kingsley Nwezeh in Abuja Operatives of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) yesterday arrested 140 suspected internet scammers also known as  yahoo boys. A statement by the commission said the suspects were nabbed in separate sting operations at popular hotels, notably,  Lakers Lounge Hotel and Bar and De Butlers, in Ikorodu, Lagos State, following credible intelligence on their involvement in internet-related fraud. However, four of the suspects were released as no incriminating item was found on them. It said the suspects were aged ages between 16 and 40 years. Items recovered from the suspects include exotic cars, electronic devices, laptop computers and mobile phones. The statement affirmed that  the suspects would be charged to court as soon as the investigations were concluded.